│     - `%cmp2 = icmp samesign uge i64 %x, %y`                                                                                 │
│     - Here, the second operand of both compares is the same (`%y`). The predicates `ult` and `uge` are inverses. When both   │
│ compares have `samesign` and the same operands, the inversion is valid. My patch incorrectly disables this optimization.     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ 2.  `@test_select_inverse_samesign_both_rhsc_same_sign`:                                                                     │
