│     - This is the case where the `ConstantRange` logic is used. When both compares have `samesign` and the constants are     │
│ positive, the logic is valid for non-negative inputs. For negative inputs, both compares are false, so they are not          │
│ inverses. The optimization is incorrect. My patch correctly disables this, but the test seems to expect it. This suggests    │
│ the test itself might be flawed, or my understanding of the `samesign` semantics with `ConstantRange` is incomplete.         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The original bug was caused by a mix of `samesign` and non-`samesign` compares.                                              │
│ - `%cmp1 = icmp ult i64 %x, 11` (no `samesign`)                                                                              │
│ - `%cmp2 = icmp samesign ugt i64 %x, 10` (`samesign`)                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The `ConstantRange` logic doesn't account for the `samesign` flag, leading to the incorrect assumption of inversion.         │
│                                                                                                                              │
