│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                      │
│ The build succeeded, but a new test `fold-a-or-b-zero.ll` is failing. This test checks for folding patterns like `(A & !B) | │
│ (!A & B)` into `A ^ B`. This optimization relies on `isKnownInversion` to identify `!A` and `!B`.                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The failing test cases involve `icmp` instructions without the `samesign` flag. My previous change was:                      │
│ ```c++                                                                                                                       │
│   if (cast<ICmpInst>(X)->hasSameSign() != cast<ICmpInst>(Y)->hasSameSign())                                                  │
│     return false;                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This code is inside `isKnownInversion`. The problem is that `isKnownInversion` can be called with `Value*` arguments that    │
│ are not `ICmpInst`s. For example, they could be `FCmpInst`s or other instructions. When `X` or `Y` is not an `ICmpInst`, the │
│ `cast<ICmpInst>` will fail, causing a crash or undefined behavior, which seems to be preventing the optimization in          │
│ `fold-a-or-b-zero.ll` from happening.                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ To fix this, I need to ensure that `X` and `Y` are indeed `ICmpInst`s before attempting to cast them and call                │
│ `hasSameSign()`. The `m_ICmp` matcher in the preceding lines does not guarantee that the `Value*` is an `ICmpInst*`. It only │
│ guarantees that it's a `CmpInst` that is an integer comparison.                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will add checks to ensure both `X` and `Y` are `ICmpInst`s before executing my `samesign` check.                           │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i '8532 a\                                                                                                              │
│   auto *ICmpX = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(X);\                                                                                      │
│   auto *ICmpY = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Y);\                                                                                      │
│   if (!ICmpX || !ICmpY)\                                                                                                     │
│     return false;\                                                                                                           │
│ \                                                                                                                            │
│   // The ConstantRange-based logic below does not account for the `samesign`\                                                │
│   // attribute, so it can incorrectly prove inversion if one compare has it\                                                 │
│   // and the other does not. Bail out if the `samesign` status differs.\                                                     │
│   if (ICmpX->hasSameSign() != ICmpY->hasSameSign())\                                                                         │
│     return false;\                                                                                                           │
│ ' llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueTracking.cpp && \                                                                                   │
│ sed -i '/if (cast<ICmpInst>(X)->hasSameSign() != cast<ICmpInst>(Y)->hasSameSign())/d' llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueTracking.cpp    │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
