│ I've made another attempt at fixing the issue. My previous change was too broad and caused a different test to fail because  │
│ I was unsafely casting `Value*` to `ICmpInst*`.                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ My new patch adds `dyn_cast` checks to ensure both values are `ICmpInst`s before checking their `samesign` status. This is   │
│ much safer.                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The new logic is:                                                                                                            │
│ ```c++                                                                                                                       │
│   auto *ICmpX = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(X);                                                                                       │
│   auto *ICmpY = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Y);                                                                                       │
│   if (!ICmpX || !ICmpY)                                                                                                      │
│     return false;                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│   // The ConstantRange-based logic below does not account for the `samesign`                                                 │
│   // attribute, so it can incorrectly prove inversion if one compare has it                                                  │
│   // and the other does not. Bail out if the `samesign` status differs.                                                      │
│   if (ICmpX->hasSameSign() != ICmpY->hasSameSign())                                                                          │
│     return false;                                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This is inserted before the `ConstantRange` logic. This should correctly handle the original bug case (mixed `samesign`)     │
│ without breaking other optimizations. The `dyn_cast` check will prevent crashes on non-`ICmpInst` values, and the `samesign` │
│ check is now safe.                                                                                                           │
